  ### Is It OK To Overlap Metal Roofing?
  
  ![regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/galleries/regal-white/regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel.jpg?width=1920&name=regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel.jpg)
  
  Corrugated metal panels must be overlapped two corrugations for roofing and one corrugations when used as siding.
  
  When using corrugated panels for roofing, you will have to purchase 10% to 12% additional corrugated.
  
  ![regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/galleries/regal-white/regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel.jpg?width=1920&name=regal-white-corrugated-metal-panel.jpg)
  
  ### What Is The Minimum Pitch For A Corrugated Metal Roof?
  
  ![black-matte-corrugated-roof](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/wsmr-gallery-page-photos/corrugated-gallery/black-matte-corrugated-roof.jpg?width=1920&name=black-matte-corrugated-roof.jpg)
  
  Corrugated is best for roofs with a slope of 3:12 or greater.
  
  If you have a roof with a lower slope than 3:12, a standing seam roof will be the better option for your home. **Mechanically fastened standing seam** panels are suitable for roof pitches of 1” in 12” or greater, or 1:12.
  
  [Learn More](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/blog/how-to-determine-roof-pitch)
  
  ![black-matte-corrugated-roof](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/wsmr-gallery-page-photos/corrugated-gallery/black-matte-corrugated-roof.jpg?width=1920&name=black-matte-corrugated-roof.jpg)
  
  ### Can You Bend Corrugated Metal Roofing?
  
  ![01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/galleries/rezibond/01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated.jpg?width=956&name=01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated.jpg)
  
  Yes, corrugated metal roofing can be bent to create a curved roof. Each panel is sent through a radius machine that bends the roofing panel to give them the desired curved shape.
  
  [Learn More](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/blog/curved-metal-roofing)
  
  ![01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/galleries/rezibond/01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated.jpg?width=956&name=01-Rezibond-Curved-Corrugated.jpg)
  
  ### What Gauge Metal Is Used For Corrugated Metal Roofing?
  
  ![corrugated-gauge-1](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/hubDB/corrugated-gauge-1.jpeg?width=1199&name=corrugated-gauge-1.jpeg)
  
  Corrugated metal panels are usually made from 26 or 24-gauge steel.
  
  We don't recommend using a 29 gauge material as the cost savings are minimal and the lifespan of the corrugated metal is significantly less.
  
  [Learn More](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/blog/29-versus-26-gauge-residential-metal-roofing-panels)
  
  ![corrugated-gauge-1](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/hubDB/corrugated-gauge-1.jpeg?width=1199&name=corrugated-gauge-1.jpeg)
  
  ### Does Corrugated Metal Rust?
  
  ![thumbnail_5 Types of Metal Roofing Thumb Pic Only](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/thumbnail_5%20Types%20of%20Metal%20Roofing%20Thumb%20Pic%20Only.jpg?width=1280&name=thumbnail_5%20Types%20of%20Metal%20Roofing%20Thumb%20Pic%20Only.jpg)
  
  Corrugated metal is extremely corrosion resistant. It's steel that has been coated with a Galvalume® coating. In addition, most corrugated metal will also have a paint system applied on top of the Galvalume®. All of these factors contribute to a metal panel that is durable and will hold up to the environment.
  
  ![thumbnail_5 Types of Metal Roofing Thumb Pic Only](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/thumbnail_5%20Types%20of%20Metal%20Roofing%20Thumb%20Pic%20Only.jpg?width=1280&name=thumbnail_5%20Types%20of%20Metal%20Roofing%20Thumb%20Pic%20Only.jpg)
  
  ### How Is A Corrugated Metal Roof Different Than A Standing Seam Metal Roof?
  
  ![corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/hubDB/corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel.jpg?width=1920&name=corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel.jpg)
  
  A corrugated metal roof features an exposed fastener system where the screws are visible while a standing seam metal roof has a concealed fastener system. The concealed fasteners makes a standing seam roof more weathertight and leak resistant compared to corrugated roofing.
  
  Corrugated metal roofs are the more economical and easier to install roofing system compared to standing seam.
  
  [Learn More](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/corrugated-metal-roofing-standing-seam)
  
  ![corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/images/hubDB/corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel.jpg?width=1920&name=corrugated-vs-standing-seam-metal-roofing-panel.jpg)
  
  ### Can A Corrugated Metal Panel Be Used For Corrugated Siding?
  
  ![black ore matte siding 3](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/facebook%20images/black%20ore%20matte%20siding%203.jpg?width=1280&name=black%20ore%20matte%20siding%203.jpg)
  
  Corrugated roofing panels can also be used as corrugated siding. Corrugated metal siding is structurally strong, impact resistant, and easy to install.
  
  [Learn More](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/blog/best-metal-siding-panels)
  
  ![black ore matte siding 3](https://www.westernstatesmetalroofing.com/hs-fs/hubfs/facebook%20images/black%20ore%20matte%20siding%203.jpg?width=1280&name=black%20ore%20matte%20siding%203.jpg)
  
